---
pagination:
  data: products
  size: 1
  alias: product
  resolve: values
permalink: "/products/{{ product.slug }}/"
layout: layouts/base.njk
eleventyComputed:
  title: "{{ product.name }}"
  description: "What {{ product.name }} contains now. Every fact is shown with its source, confidence and evidence level; anything not yet verified is withheld rather than asserted."
---
{% from "components/macros.njk" import sourcedValue, sourceNote, caveatBox %}

{#
  One server-rendered page per product. The src/_data/products/* cascade is an
  OBJECT keyed by filename, so the front-matter pagination uses resolve: values:
  default pagination over an object iterates its KEYS (strings), which would break
  every template (03a-RESEARCH.md Pattern 1 / Pitfall 2). Hyphenated keys
  (products.spike-01) are also invalid Nunjucks dot access; paginating over values
  sidesteps that. A1 is smoke-verified by asserting the product NAME (not a
  filename) renders on a built page.
#}

<h1>{{ product.name }}</h1>

<p class="lede">The current declared record for {{ product.name }}. Each value is shown through the trust component: a fact appears only once it has met the verification standard its claim type demands, and is otherwise marked "not yet verified; withheld".</p>

{#
  Sections follow the LOCKED D-05 order: Ingredients, Nutrition, Allergens,
  Manufacturer, Sources, Recipe history. This plan (03a-03) authors Ingredients,
  Manufacturer, Sources and Recipe history. Plan 04 inserts the Nutrition and
  Allergens h2 sections between Ingredients and Manufacturer, in that order; the
  placeholder comment below marks where they slot in so the outline stays gap-free.
#}

<section id="ingredients" aria-labelledby="ingredients-heading">
  <h2 id="ingredients-heading">Ingredients</h2>
  <p>The current declared ingredients list. This is the sourced recipe of record; it is not broken out into individual ingredient entries here.</p>
  {%- if product.ingredientsText %}
  {{ sourcedValue(product.ingredientsText, sources.sources, "Declared ingredients", "", "product") }}
  {%- else %}
  <p class="example">No declared ingredients list has been sourced for this product yet.</p>
  {%- endif %}
</section>

{# PLAN 04 INSERTS HERE, in D-05 order:
   <section id="nutrition"> ... </section>  (the nutrition table, D-06)
   <section id="allergens"> ... </section>  (the allergen fail-safe list, D-12)
   Do not reorder; Manufacturer, Sources and Recipe history must stay after them. #}

<section id="manufacturer" aria-labelledby="manufacturer-heading">
  <h2 id="manufacturer-heading">Manufacturer</h2>
  {%- if product.manufacturer %}
  {{ sourcedValue(product.manufacturer, sources.sources, "Made by", "", "product") }}
  {%- else %}
  <p class="example">No manufacturer has been sourced for this product yet.</p>
  {%- endif %}
</section>
</content>
